All endpoints require:

Tenant header

Signature validation

11️⃣ Security Enhancements

Mandatory enterprise additions:

HMAC signature validation

Per-tenant rate limiting

Origin domain enforcement

Encrypted API keys

Structured logging

Token usage tracking

Abuse detection

12️⃣ Docker Deployment Model

Single stack:

docker-compose.yml
  - backend
  - postgres
  - redis (optional)

All tenants run in same backend container.

Isolation enforced at:

Application layer

Database row level

Middleware validation

13️⃣ Scaling Strategy

Short-term:

Single VPS

Vertical scaling

Mid-term:

Load balancer

Multiple backend replicas

Shared DB

Long-term:

Kubernetes

Optional dedicated deployment tier for enterprise clients

14️⃣ Implementation Roadmap
Phase 1 – Database Refactor

Add tenant_id everywhere

Create tenants table

Migrate existing single client to tenant record

Phase 2 – Middleware

Build tenant validation layer

Build API key injection layer

Phase 3 – Admin Dashboard

Tenant CRUD

API key management

Avatar assignment

Phase 4 – Widget Security

HMAC signature system

Domain validation

Phase 5 – Logging & Analytics

Token usage per tenant

Conversation metrics

15️⃣ Enterprise Guarantees

✔ Strict tenant isolation
✔ Separate API billing
✔ No context leakage
✔ Centralized management
✔ Docker-native deployment
✔ Future-ready for subscription billing

16️⃣ Risk Considerations

API key misuse if not encrypted

Widget script copying between domains

High token cost if rate limiting absent

Missing usage caps before billing launch

Mitigation required before public release.

